# Modal Component Rules for Admin Web Pages

## 🎯 Purpose

This rule defines comprehensive rules and best practices for implementing modal dialogs in **admin web pages** (`/adminWeb/*`). Admin pages use three types of modals: **Modal Component**, **ConfirmDialog Component**, and **Custom Inline Modals**.

**Key Context:**

- ✅ Modal and ConfirmDialog components are located in `@/shared/ui/adminWeb`
- ✅ Custom CSS classes are defined in `@/shared/styles/admin/dialog.css`
- ✅ Modals are primarily used in admin pages for complex interactions

---

## 📋 Modal Types

### Type 1: Modal Component (`@/shared/ui/adminWeb/Modal`)

**Purpose**: General-purpose modal for displaying complex content (forms, trees, lists, data tables)

**Characteristics:**

- ✅ Flexible size options: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`
- ✅ Custom title and close button support
- ✅ ESC key support (automatic)
- ✅ Body scroll lock when open (automatic)
- ✅ Overlay click to close
- ✅ Uses `modal-container` and `modal-content` CSS classes from `dialog.css`

**When to Use:**

- Displaying complex content (trees, forms, data tables)
- Content that requires scrolling
- Multi-step workflows
- Content selection modals
- Menu tree displays
- Large data displays

**Location:** `src/shared/ui/admin/Modal.tsx`

### Type 2: ConfirmDialog Component (`@/shared/ui/adminWeb/ConfirmDialog`)

**Purpose**: Simple confirmation dialogs for user actions

**Characteristics:**

- ✅ Fixed size (max-w-[450px])
- ✅ Icon-based type system: `danger`, `warning`, `success`
- ✅ Two-button layout (Cancel/Confirm)
- ✅ Uses `dialog-container` and `dialog-content` CSS classes from `dialog.css`
- ✅ Centered content layout

**When to Use:**

- Delete confirmations
- Save/Update confirmations
- Warning messages
- Success notifications (after create/update operations)
- Simple yes/no questions

**Location:** `src/shared/ui/admin/ConfirmDialog.tsx`

### Type 3: Custom Inline Modals

**Purpose**: Page-specific modals that don't fit standard patterns

**Characteristics:**

- ✅ Implemented directly in page components
- ✅ Custom structure and behavior
- ✅ Must follow styling guidelines from this rule

**When to Use:**

- Highly specialized UI requirements
- Complex interactions not covered by standard components
- Legacy code migration (should be refactored to use Modal component when possible)

---

## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Component Selection

**MUST follow this decision tree when implementing modals:**

```
Need a modal in admin page?
├─ Simple confirmation/alert?
│  └─ YES → Use ConfirmDialog
│     ├─ Delete action? → type="danger"
│     ├─ Warning message? → type="warning"
│     └─ Success message (after create/update)? → type="success"
│
└─ Complex content (form, tree, list, table)?
   └─ YES → Use Modal Component
      ├─ Small content? → size="sm" (448px)
      ├─ Medium content? → size="md" (672px) - DEFAULT
      ├─ Large content? → size="lg" (896px)
      └─ Extra large? → size="xl" (1152px)
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Use ConfirmDialog for complex content (forms, trees, lists)
- ❌ Use Modal component for simple yes/no confirmations
- ❌ Create custom inline modals when standard components suffice

---

## 📦 Modal Component Usage

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Import and Basic Structure

**MUST:**

```typescript
import { Modal } from "@/shared/ui/adminWeb";

// State management
const [isModalOpen, setIsModalOpen] = useState(false);

// Open handler
const handleOpenModal = () => {
  setIsModalOpen(true);
};

// Close handler with cleanup
const handleCloseModal = () => {
  setIsModalOpen(false);
  // Reset form/data if needed
  setFormData(initialFormData);
  setErrors({});
};

// Usage
<Modal
  isOpen={isModalOpen}
  title="Modal Title"
  onClose={handleCloseModal}
  size="md" // or "sm", "lg", "xl"
  showCloseButton={true}
>
  {/* Modal content */}
</Modal>;
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Import from wrong path (must be `@/shared/ui/adminWeb`)
- ❌ Use inline styles for positioning (CSS classes handle this automatically)
- ❌ Forget to handle state cleanup on close
- ❌ Use `dialog-container` or `dialog-content` classes directly (those are for ConfirmDialog)
- ❌ Skip CSS import (`@/shared/styles/admin/dialog.css` is imported in Modal component)

### Size Guidelines

**MUST use appropriate size based on content:**

| Size | Max Width | Use Case                        | Example                |
| ---- | --------- | ------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `sm` | 448px     | Simple forms, small selections  | Single input forms     |
| `md` | 672px     | Standard forms, medium lists    | Default for most cases |
| `lg` | 896px     | Large forms, data tables, trees | Menu tree displays     |
| `xl` | 1152px    | Complex dashboards, wide tables | Data analysis views    |

**Reference Implementation:**

- ✅ `src/features/adminWeb/menu/make/ui/MenuMakePageView.tsx` uses `size="lg"` for menu tree

### Content Structure

**MUST:**

```tsx
<Modal isOpen={isOpen} title="Title" onClose={onClose} size="md">
  {/* Handle loading state */}
  {loading ? (
    <div className="p-8 text-center">
      <div className="inline-block animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-blue-600"></div>
      <p className="mt-4 text-gray-600">Loading...</p>
    </div>
  ) : error ? (
    <div className="p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-red-700">
      {error}
    </div>
  ) : (
    <div className="space-y-4">{/* Your content here */}</div>
  )}
</Modal>
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Put content directly without wrapper divs
- ❌ Use fixed heights without overflow handling
- ❌ Forget to handle loading/error states
- ❌ Skip proper spacing between content elements

