### ⚠️ CRITICAL: API Communication Error Handling Pattern

**MUST ALWAYS check existing registration form patterns before implementing API error handling when:**

- ✅ Creating new registration/edit forms
- ✅ Implementing form submission error handling
- ✅ Handling API communication errors (ApiError, network errors, etc.)
- ✅ Displaying error messages after API calls
- ✅ Ensuring consistency across all admin forms

**MUST ensure all API communication errors are displayed using ConfirmDialog ONLY, not red text messages above forms.**

---

## 🎯 Root Cause Analysis of Common Mistakes

### Pattern Ignorance: Not Checking Existing Codebase Patterns

**Why This Rule Exists:**

All admin registration/edit forms in this codebase follow a **consistent pattern** for API error handling:

1. ❌ **WRONG**: Using `setError()` to display API errors as red text above forms
2. ✅ **CORRECT**: Using `ConfirmDialog` with `type="danger"` for all API communication errors

**Real-world example of the mistake:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG: Displaying API errors as red text
catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof ApiError) {
    setError(err.message); // ❌ Inconsistent with other forms
    // Missing ConfirmDialog for API errors
  }
}

// In component:
{error && <div className="p-6 text-center text-red-600">{error}</div>} // ❌ Red text above form
```

**Why this is wrong:**

- ❌ Creates inconsistent user experience (some forms show red text, others show dialogs)
- ❌ Users may miss errors that appear above the form (less visible than modal dialogs)
- ❌ Does not match the established pattern used in all other admin registration forms

**MUST:**

- ✅ **ALWAYS** check existing registration forms (`MemberRegisterForm`, `BoardRegisterForm`, `ProgramRegisterForm`) before implementing error handling
- ✅ **ALWAYS** use ConfirmDialog for API communication errors
- ✅ **ALWAYS** use `type="danger"` for API error dialogs (NOT "error")
- ✅ **ALWAYS** initialize `error` state but use it only for non-API errors (pre-submission validation, etc.)

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ **NEVER** use `setError()` for API communication errors
- ❌ **NEVER** display API errors as red text above forms
- ❌ **NEVER** use `type="error"` (correct type is "danger")
- ❌ **NEVER** implement error handling without checking existing patterns
- ❌ **NEVER** mix error display methods (ConfirmDialog + red text)

