## 🎨 CSS Classes and Styling

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: CSS Import

**MUST:**

- ✅ Modal and ConfirmDialog components automatically import `@/shared/styles/admin/dialog.css`
- ✅ For custom inline modals, CSS classes are handled via Tailwind classes (no additional import needed)

**CSS Classes Reference:**

#### Modal Component Classes (from dialog.css)

```css
.modal-container {
  /* Centered positioning, animation */
  /* Size controlled by Tailwind classes (max-w-md, max-w-2xl, etc.) */
}

.modal-content {
  /* White background, rounded corners (rounded-lg), shadow, padding */
}
```

#### ConfirmDialog Classes (from dialog.css)

```css
.dialog-container {
  /* Fixed size: max-w-[450px] */
  /* Centered positioning */
}

.dialog-content {
  /* White background, rounded corners, shadow */
}
```

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Use `modal-container` or `modal-content` classes directly in custom code (only Modal component uses these)
- ❌ Use `dialog-container` or `dialog-content` classes in Modal component (those are for ConfirmDialog)
- ❌ Mix CSS classes between Modal and ConfirmDialog

### Border Radius Standards

**MUST:**

- ✅ Use `rounded-lg` for all modal containers (standard across project)
- ✅ Use `rounded-t-lg` for headers (top corners only)
- ✅ Use `rounded-b-lg` for content areas (bottom corners only)
- ✅ Use `overflow-hidden` to preserve rounded corners

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Mix different border radius values (`rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`, etc.)
- ❌ Forget `overflow-hidden` (breaks rounded appearance)
- ❌ Use inconsistent border radius across different modals

### Shadow Standards

**MUST:**

- ✅ Use `shadow-lg` for modal containers
- ✅ Use `shadow-2xl` for ConfirmDialog (defined in CSS, automatic)

