## ✅ Best Practices

### 1. State Management

**MUST:**

```typescript
// Single source of truth
const [isModalOpen, setIsModalOpen] = useState(false);

// Clear naming
const handleOpenModal = () => setIsModalOpen(true);
const handleCloseModal = () => {
  setIsModalOpen(false);
  // Cleanup: reset form, clear errors, etc.
  setFormData(initialFormData);
  setErrors({});
};
```

### 2. Loading States

**MUST:**

```tsx
<Modal isOpen={isOpen} title="Loading..." onClose={onClose}>
  {loading ? (
    <div className="p-8 text-center">
      <div className="inline-block animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-blue-600"></div>
      <p className="mt-4 text-gray-600">Loading...</p>
    </div>
  ) : (
    <Content />
  )}
</Modal>
```

### 3. Error Handling

**MUST:**

```tsx
<Modal isOpen={isOpen} title="Error" onClose={onClose}>
  {error ? (
    <div className="p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-red-700">
      {error}
    </div>
  ) : (
    <Content />
  )}
</Modal>
```

### 4. Body Scroll Lock

**MUST:**

- ✅ Modal component handles this automatically
- ✅ For custom modals, implement manually:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (isModalOpen) {
    document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
  }
  return () => {
    document.body.style.overflow = "unset";
  };
}, [isModalOpen]);
```

### 5. Multiple Modals

**MUST:**

```typescript
// Use separate state for each modal
const [showModal1, setShowModal1] = useState(false);
const [showModal2, setShowModal2] = useState(false);

// Ensure only one modal is open at a time
const handleOpenModal1 = () => {
  setShowModal2(false); // Close other modals
  setShowModal1(true);
};
```

